{{HeadingA|Macros in Project Ascension}}
Macros allow players to automate complex actions, streamline combat, and customize gameplay in powerful ways. While they may seem intimidating at first, filled with syntax, conditionals, and modifiers, learning how macros work unlocks a new level of gameplay control. 
=== What is a Macro? ===
A '''macro''' is a user-defined command or script that combines multiple game functions into a single button press. You can use macros to:

* Cast spells on specific targets
* Use items or trinkets
* Create mouseover healing, ground-targeted AoEs, or mod-shift abilities
* Automate condition-based behaviors

== Useful Macros ==

=== Transmog collection macro ===
/run local c=C_AppearanceCollection for b=0,4 do for s=1,GetContainerNumSlots(b) do local i=GetContainerItemID(b,s) local a=i and C_Appearance.GetItemAppearanceID(i) if a and not c.IsAppearanceCollected(a) then c.CollectItemAppearance(i) end end end

