{{HeadingA|Targeting Conditions in Macros & Spellcasting}}
Targeting conditions are used in macros to '''control who or what your spell or ability is cast on''', based on specific rules. They help automate logic like “cast on myself if no target,” “cast on friendly mouseover,” or “cast only if my target is alive.”

These conditions are built into macros using '''<code>[condition]</code>''' brackets, and you can chain them for complex logic.
=== Basic Targeting Conditions ===
{| class="fandom-table"
!Condition
!What It Does
|-
|<code>@target</code>
|Casts on your current target
|-
|<code>@focus</code>
|Casts on your focus target
|-
|<code>@mouseover</code>
|Casts on the unit your mouse is hovering over
|-
|<code>@player</code>
|Casts on yourself
|-
|<code>@pet</code>
|Casts on your pet
|-
|<code>@party1</code>–<code>@party4</code>
|Casts on specific party members (group order)
|-
|<code>@raid1</code>–<code>@raid40</code>
|Casts on specific raid members
|}
