=== Example Macro Logic ===

==== Smart Heal ====
 <code>/cast [@mouseover,help,nodead] [@target,help,nodead] [@player] Flash Heal</code>
🔹 Heals mouseover target > your selected friendly target > yourself

==== Utility with Modifiers ====
 <code>/cast [mod:alt,@player] Power Word: Shield; [@target,help,nodead] Power Word: Shield</code>
🔹 Shields your target unless you hold '''Alt''', then it shields you

==== Battle Rez Priority ====
 <code>/cast [@mouseover,dead,help] [@target,dead,help] Rebirth</code>
🔹 Casts Rebirth on a dead friendly target, prioritizing your mouseover
=== Notes for Targeting Logic ===

* Conditions are evaluated in order—the first valid one is used.
* Use <code>,</code> (commas) to group fallback logic, and <code>;</code> to separate condition sets.
* Combine multiple conditions like <code>[@target, exists, harm, nodead]</code> for safer macro logic.
* <code>[noexists]</code> is shorthand for "target doesn't exist" and is great for self-casting defaults.

{{HeadingA|Mouseover Macros}}
Mouseover macros let you cast a spell on a unit you're hovering over '''without changing targets'''.
 <code>#showtooltip
 /cast [@mouseover,exists,nodead] Flash Heal; Flash Heal</code>
If you're hovering over a unit, it heals them. If not, it heals your current target. Simple and powerful.
{{HeadingA|Priority System: Order Matters}}
Macro logic follows a '''top-down priority''':

* The macro reads from '''left to right''', executing the first '''true''' condition it finds.
* Example:

 <code>/cast [@mouseover,exists,nodead] Smite; [@focus,exists,nodead] Smite; Smite</code>
This says:

# If I have a mouseover, cast Smite at that.
# Else, if I have a focus target, cast at them.
# Else, cast at my current target.

This allows '''fall-through behavior''' that adapts to your situation.
{{HeadingA|Modifier Macros}}
You can use keyboard '''modifiers''' like Shift, Ctrl, or Alt to dynamically change the behavior of a macro.
 <code>/cast [mod:shift] Greater Heal; Heal</code>

* Pressing Shift casts Greater Heal.
* Pressing nothing casts Heal.

This is great for combining '''multiple spells into a single keybind'''.
{{HeadingA|At-Cursor and At-Player Casting}}
Targeted AoE spells like ''Death and Decay'' or ''Mass Dispel'' often use ground reticles. You can remove the reticle delay with <code>@cursor</code> or cast them at your feet with <code>@player</code>.

=== At Cursor: ===
 <code>/cast [@cursor] Death and Decay</code>

=== At Player: ===
 <code>/cast [mod:shift,@player] Death and Decay; [@cursor] Death and Decay</code>
This version casts:

* At your feet when holding Shift
* At your cursor otherwise

{{HeadingA|Cast Sequence Macros}}
Cast sequences are advanced macros that execute '''spells in order'''.
 <code>/castsequence reset=10 Spell1, Spell2, Spell3</code>

* Spells are cast in sequence with each button press.
* The sequence resets after 10 seconds of inactivity.

Great for opening rotations or utility combos.
{{HeadingA|Common Macro Templates}}

=== Heal on Mouseover or Target ===
 <code>#showtooltip
 /cast [@mouseover,exists,nodead] Flash Heal; Flash Heal</code>

=== One-Button AoE with Modifier ===
 <code>#showtooltip
 /cast [mod:shift,@player] Consecration; [@cursor] Consecration</code>

=== Focus Interrupt ===
 <code>#showtooltip
 /cast [@focus,exists,nodead] Kick</code>
== Tips and Troubleshooting ==

* '''Capitalize''' spell names (e.g., <code>Smite</code>, not <code>smite</code>)
* Use <code>exists</code> and <code>nodead</code> to prevent macro failure
* Use <code>/use</code> instead of <code>/cast</code> for trinkets and items
* Be mindful of '''global cooldowns''' when chaining multiple casts

